The paper discusses a security attack on wireless keyboards, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The attack involves eavesdropping on the communication channel used by the keyboard, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the algorithmic machinery used in the attack, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses potential countermeasures and future research directions, which could fall under the category of multimedia (cs.MM) if the countermeasures involve audio or video signals.
